The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Piramyd issue priced at Rs 120

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Nov. 18: Piramyd Retail Ltd has fixed the issue price of its initial public offering at Rs 120 per share ? the lowest end of the price band. The issue was over-subscribed 11.62 times. 

 The retailer had entered the capital market on November 20 with a public issue of 90 lakh shares and offered a price band of Rs 120-140 for book building. 

 Out of the total shares, 40 lakh were allotted to the promoters and the balance 50 lakh shares were the net offer to the public. 

 The public holding will constitute 25 per cent of the companys post-issue paid-up capital of Rs 20 crore.

 Piramyd plans to deploy the net proceeds from the issue for funding its capital expenditure requirements, upgradation of information technology infrastructure and repayment of bridge loans.

 The book-running lead managers of the issue were Enam Financial Consultants Pvt Ltd, DSP Merrill Lynch Ltd and Edelweiss Capital Ltd.

 The issue closed on November 16. And at the lower end of the price band, the company raised Rs 108 crore.




